<script type="text/javascript">podPressShowHidePlayer('1', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2010/3-10/epi-00401-rvs-as-a-prep.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress//images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-401- RVs as a Prep', 'The Survival Podcast');</script><p>I just bought a brand new Shamrock 21SS RV and thought it was a good excuse to do a show on RVs as a prep.Â  I am also mobile today doing a show from the personal mobile studio which seems fitting for the discussion on RVs.</p>
<p>Also &#8211; Please do me a favor and watch, comment, vote on this video of <a target="_blank" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=307U-RKkJ8Q" target="_blank">The Shelf Reliance Harvest 72 Rack System</a>.</p>
<p>Join me today as we discuss&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li>RVs are &#8220;not quite a home on wheels&#8221;</li>
<li>The advantages of mobility</li>
<li>The ease of adding solar power to an RV</li>
<li>Power expansion and avoiding over kill</li>
<li>Propane &#8211; more is better</li>
<li>Thoughts on generators and why NOT to buy one from an RV salesman</li>
<li>Weight considerations for your two vehicle</li>
<li>Motor-coach vs. two vehicle, advantages and disadvantages of both</li>
<li>Limits to being &#8220;self contained&#8221; and dealing with gray/black water</li>
<li>Thoughts on storing your RV</li>
<li>Accessories and thoughts on research before you buy</li>
</ul>
